# ADR-019: the trust-bearing surfaces — the gates, the audit, the agent
# tooling, and the workflows that run them — are owned. With the repository
# setting "require review from Code Owners" enabled (docs/security-checklist.md),
# a PR touching these paths cannot auto-merge on gate-green alone; swarm prove
# PRs never touch them and are unaffected.
/.github/        @cgbarlow
/tools/gate_a/   @cgbarlow
/tools/gate_b/   @cgbarlow
/AxiomAudit/     @cgbarlow
/AuditFixtures/  @cgbarlow
/swarm/          @cgbarlow
/lakefile.toml   @cgbarlow
/lean-toolchain  @cgbarlow

# ADR-078/080/081 (#5643): the benchmark/target intake + scoring trust surfaces.
# The target registry, the intake validator, the domain-admission registry/predicate,
# and the credit/scoring generator must not auto-merge on gate-green alone — they
# decide what is admitted to the commons and what earns board credit.
/targets/           @cgbarlow
/tools/intake/      @cgbarlow
/tools/governance/  @cgbarlow
/docs/governance/   @cgbarlow
/tools/leaderboard/ @cgbarlow
